trials.freeResponse: Daxes beep. Every single Dax tested emitted one, so I assume they all do.
All wugs boom, since I tested over 20 of them and all of them boomed.
Griffs whistle, but only sometimes. Some griffs whistle, others don't. The odds of a griff whistling is roughly 50%
Blickets don't squeak. There are rare cases where it happens, but the odds of that are roughly 1/15. The majority of the blickets definitely do not produce any sounds.

Tomas don't click. At least generally. The toma given to me by my colleague clicked, but none of the ones I tested myself. So either the tomas do click, but in extremely rare cases or there was something different about that particular toma.
Feps ring sometimes and other times they don't, with the odds of them ringing being slightly higher than them not ringing (11/20 or slightly over 50%)

trials.response: I tested various materials that were inspected by other scientists before me and was asked to determine if the objects in question did indeed produce the sounds in question, what the probability of that happening was and what I learned about those objects after testing them myself.
